  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies the arguments used to customize a typeface, including variation positions, collection index, and palette settings.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a lightweight `ref struct` used to pass customization
parameters when cloning a <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface> via
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone*>. It bundles variation design position,
collection index, palette index, and per-entry palette color overrides into
a single value.

Because it is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap or boxed.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 },
    },
};
using var boldTypeface = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
